 like I should explore using `String.class.getMethod(\\\"toString\\\")` to simplify testing.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing method overriding**\\n\\nI’ve got this piece of code that’s checking if `String` is overriding the `toString` method from `Object`, and it looks concise, with empty parameters. I’m considering whether `String` is a final class, but since the method is public and an override, that seems okay. It doesn’t rely on upstream library types, just the ReflectionNavigator, which is good for less integration. It might even mean that there’s coverage for a line from the $10 mark, which is interesting!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_A6BG8DEjAzqvcKDKKiVDeY8S|fc_08e5bb05000e89b70169f06fdf605c8190a64cb08e67a8f96f", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.glassfish.jaxb/jaxb-core/3.0.0-M5/src/test/java/org_glassfish_jaxb/jaxb_core/ReflectionNavigatorAnonymous10Test.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_glassfish_jaxb.jaxb_core;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Field;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Type;\n\nimport org.glassfish.jaxb.core.v2.model.nav.Navigator;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class ReflectionNavigatorAnonymous10Test {\n    @Test\n    public void detectsMethodOverridingSuperclassDeclaration() throws Exception {\n        Navigator<Type, Class<?>, Field, Method> navigator = navigator();\n        Method method = String.class.getMethod(\"toString\");\n\n        assertThat(navigator.isOverriding(method, Object.class)).isTrue();\n    }\n\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"unchecked\")\n    private static Navigator<Type, Class<?>, Field, Method> navigator() throws Exception {\n        Class<?> navigatorType = Class.forName(\"org.glassfish.jaxb.core.v2.model.nav.ReflectionNavigator\");\n        Method getInstance = navigatorType.getDeclaredMethod(\"getInstance\");\n        getInstance.setAccessible(true);\n        return (Navigator<Type, Class<?>, Field, Method>) getInstance.invoke(null);\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1494, "output": 1068, "cacheRead": 30208, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32770, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777364947693, "responseId": "resp_08e5bb05000e89b70169f06fd425088190bfc133381f99edca"}}
